The only difference to outgoing connections is that the internal actor managing the listen port—the sender of the Bound message—watches the actor which was named as the recipient for Connected messages in the Bind messageTcpMessage.bind method. When that actor terminates the listen port will be closed and all resources associated with it will be released; existing connections will not be terminated at this point.

